1978.name: How much we think we spend on health expenditure (IPSOS (2016))
1978.description: Percentage of GDP the average person thinks its country spends on health expenditure per year
1978.datasetName: Perceptions of spending on health expenditure - IPSOS (2016)
1978.s_name: Perceptions of spending on health expenditure - IPSOS (2016)

source.name: Perceptions of spending on health expenditure - IPSOS (2016)
source.dataPublishedBy: Ipsos MORI Perils of Perception Study 2016
source.additionalInfo:
Ipsos MORI conducted 27,250 interviews across 50 countries between September-November 2016 via the Ipsos MORI Online Panel system. In the Czech Republic, Montenegro, Netherlands, Norway and Serbia, interviews were carried out through a combination of the online system and face-to-face methodologies.

Data are weighted to match the profile of the population.
